Thirty six prisoners have been injured following a fire incident at the Leeuwkop prison in Johannesburg on Friday.Reports from the scene indicate that thirty six people sustained serious to minor injuries and two prisoners are in a critical condition.Netcare 911 said paramedics are on scene with various emergency services.&#8220;Paramedics are busy treating the prisoners for smoke inhalation and burn wounds.&#8220;Those who require further medical care will be transported to various hospitals in Johannesburg for further medical care,&#8221; Netcare 911 said.The exact detail as to what happened will form part of a SAPS investigation and comment.-TNA Reporter